es.uam.eps.ir.ranksys.fast.preference

Class TransposedPreferenceData<I,U,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.uam.eps.ir.ranksys.fast.preference.TransposedPreferenceData<I,U,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - type of the items
    U - type of the users
    O - type of other information about preferences
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ItemIndex<U>, UserIndex<I>, PreferenceData<I,U,O>, FastItemIndex<U>, FastUserIndex<I>, FastPreferenceData<I,U,O>

    public class TransposedPreferenceData<I,U,O>
extends Object
implements FastPreferenceData<I,U,O>
    Transposed preferences, where users and items change roles. This class is useful to simplify the implementation of many algorithms that work user or item-wise, such as similarities or matrix factorization.
    Author:
    Sa√∫l Vargas (saul.vargas@uam.es)
